ute 'ssh-keygen' to create local keys; accept all defaults by pressing &lt;Enter&gt;. \u00a0Then copy your\u00a0<em>public<\/em> key:<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0 $ cat ~\/.ssh\/id_rsa.pub<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Copy and paste that text. On\u00a0MacOS, you can use the 'pbcopy' (pasteboard copy) command:<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0 $ pbcopy &lt; ~\/.ssh\/id_rsa.pub<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>In the HPC terminal, open '~\/.ssh\/authorized_keys' and add the line of text from the 'id_rsa.pub.' \u00a0If the file does not exist, create it. \u00a0Ensure that the permissions on the file are 600 ('chmod 600').<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>"},"is_project":0}],"available_protocols":[]},{"id":"168332","is_changed":0,"original_id":"0","is_skipped":"0","is_checked":"0","guid":"A3476215200A4A13B90FF609F57A1D42","previous_guid":"1D98EDB2F105474D93B143C5233F27D6","previous_id":"168323","last_modified":"1502718889","components":[{"component_id":"984715","previous_id":0,"original_id":"0","guid":"6CE1BE6360EA438FB73FB14CED6215BC","previous_guid":null,"component_type_id":"6","data_id":null,"data":null,"order_id":"0","name":"Section","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"6","source_data":{"section":null},"is_project":0},{"component_id":"194954","previous_id":"984715","original_id":"0","guid":"CDB32D8FBC3E48F6BF58CBD24EF1A9E9","previous_guid":"6CE1BE6360EA438FB73FB14CED6215BC","component_type_id":"1","data_id":"0","data":"<p><strong>Test no-password login<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Back in your\u00a0<em>local<\/em> terminal, test\u00a0that you can login without 2-factor auth by executing 'ssh &lt;NetID&gt;@hpc.arizona.edu'. \u00a0If you were logged in automatically, you are all set.<\/p>","order_id":"1","name":"Description","data_by_id":"0","type_id":"1","source_data":{"description":"<p><strong>Test no-password login<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Back in your\u00a0<em>local<\/em> terminal, test\u00a0that you can login without 2-factor auth 